# Autodesk APS MCP-only

When answering APS/API questions (or when using `/autodesk-aps`):

- Answer APS questions **only** via the **`autodesk-aps`** MCP server.
- Do not read `examples/`, or `server.py` unless the user asks about MCP server code.
- Prefer MCP resources `aps://catalog/*` for browsing; use tools for search, details, auth status, and live GET.
- Always name the MCP tool(s) used in the response.
- For user-specific questions ("I", "my", "me"; e.g. my hubs, my projects), call `aps_auth_status` first. If `user_context_available` is false, do not call `aps_live_get`. Tell the user to set `APS_ACCESS_TOKEN` (three-legged token) in `.env`. Client ID and secret are app-level only, not user context.
